<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1436,639,1060]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,784,808]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Galil" authorityYear="2009" box="[328,504,784,808]" class="Malacostraca" family="Leucosiidae" genus="Hiplyra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sagitta">
<emphasis box="[328,504,784,808]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Hiplyra sagitta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was recently described from the Persian 
<collectingRegion box="[1009,1060,783,807]" country="Papua New Guinea" name="Gulf" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Gulf</collectingRegion>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Galil, B. S." box="[1114,1261,783,807]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="279 - 320" refId="ref47241" refString="Galil, B. S. (2009) An examination of the genus Philyra Leach, 1817 (Crustacea, Decapoda, Leucosiidae) with description of seven new genera and six new species. Zoosystema, 31 (2), 279 - 320." type="journal article" year="2009">Galil (2009)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<typeStatus box="[1278,1382,783,807]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Holotype</typeStatus>
and 
<typeStatus box="[151,258,820,844]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">paratypes</typeStatus>
described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Galil, B. S." box="[437,582,820,844]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="279 - 320" refId="ref47241" refString="Galil, B. S. (2009) An examination of the genus Philyra Leach, 1817 (Crustacea, Decapoda, Leucosiidae) with description of seven new genera and six new species. Zoosystema, 31 (2), 279 - 320." type="journal article" year="2009">Galil (2009)</bibRefCitation>
are from Danish Expedition material collected in 1937 from 
<collectingRegion box="[1343,1436,820,844]" country="Iran" name="Bushehr" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Bushehr</collectingRegion>
published by 
<bibRefCitation author="Stephensen, K." box="[307,518,855,879]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="57 - 237" refId="ref52943" refString="Stephensen, K. (1946) The Brachyura of the Iranian Gulf. Danish Scientific Investigations in Iran, Part IV. E. Munksgaard, Copenhagen, 57 - 237." type="book chapter" year="1946">Stephensen (1946)</bibRefCitation>
under the name of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Ruppell" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[747,947,856,880]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Philyra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="variegata">
<emphasis box="[747,947,856,880]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Philyra variegata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Apel, M." box="[964,1103,855,879]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" refId="ref45060" refString="Apel, M. (2001) Taxonomie und Zoogeographie der Brachyura, Paguridea und Porcellanidae (Crustacea: Decapoda) des Persisch-Arabischen Golfes. Unpublished doctoral thesis, Johann Wolfgang Goethe-Universitat, Frankfurt a. M., 268 pp." type="book" year="2001">Apel (2001)</bibRefCitation>
had re-examined material of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Ruppell" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[151,354,892,916]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Philyra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="variegata">
<emphasis box="[151,354,892,916]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Philyra variegata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of 
<bibRefCitation author="Stephensen, K." box="[403,617,892,916]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="57 - 237" refId="ref52943" refString="Stephensen, K. (1946) The Brachyura of the Iranian Gulf. Danish Scientific Investigations in Iran, Part IV. E. Munksgaard, Copenhagen, 57 - 237." type="book chapter" year="1946">Stephensen (1946)</bibRefCitation>
from Jask and mentioned that there are two new species within the material. 
<taxonomicName authority="Naderloo &amp; Türkay, 2012" authorityName="Naderloo &amp; Türkay" authorityYear="2012" box="[259,343,928,952]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Philyra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[259,343,928,952]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Philyra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[352,416,927,951]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
1 of 
<bibRefCitation author="Apel, M." box="[469,607,927,951]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" refId="ref45060" refString="Apel, M. (2001) Taxonomie und Zoogeographie der Brachyura, Paguridea und Porcellanidae (Crustacea: Decapoda) des Persisch-Arabischen Golfes. Unpublished doctoral thesis, Johann Wolfgang Goethe-Universitat, Frankfurt a. M., 268 pp." type="book" year="2001">Apel (2001)</bibRefCitation>
has been later described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Galil, B. S." box="[936,1076,927,951]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="279 - 320" refId="ref47241" refString="Galil, B. S. (2009) An examination of the genus Philyra Leach, 1817 (Crustacea, Decapoda, Leucosiidae) with description of seven new genera and six new species. Zoosystema, 31 (2), 279 - 320." type="journal article" year="2009">Galil (2009)</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Galil" authorityYear="2009" box="[1117,1290,928,952]" class="Malacostraca" family="Leucosiidae" genus="Hiplyra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sagitta">
<emphasis box="[1117,1290,928,952]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Hiplyra sagitta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The second new species distinguished by 
<bibRefCitation author="Apel, M." box="[486,623,964,988]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" refId="ref45060" refString="Apel, M. (2001) Taxonomie und Zoogeographie der Brachyura, Paguridea und Porcellanidae (Crustacea: Decapoda) des Persisch-Arabischen Golfes. Unpublished doctoral thesis, Johann Wolfgang Goethe-Universitat, Frankfurt a. M., 268 pp." type="book" year="2001">Apel (2001)</bibRefCitation>
within the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Ruppell" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[752,887,964,988]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Philyra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="variegata">
<emphasis box="[752,766,965,988]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[780,887,965,988]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">variegata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been assigned to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Gravier, 1920)" baseAuthorityName="Gravier" baseAuthorityYear="1920" box="[1134,1436,964,988]" class="Malacostraca" family="Palaemonidae" genus="Kemponia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elegans">
<emphasis box="[1134,1154,965,988]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1169,1254,964,988]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">elegans</emphasis>
(Gravier, 1920)
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Naderloo, R. &amp; Apel, M." box="[187,468,999,1023]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="248 - 258" refId="ref50320" refString="Naderloo, R. &amp; Apel, M. (2012) Leucosiid crabs of the genus Hiplyra Galil, 2009 (Crustacea; Brachyura; Leucosiidae) from the Persian Gulf and the Gulf of Oman with describing a new species. Zoological studies, 52 (2), 248 - 258." type="journal article" year="2012">Naderloo &amp; Apel (2012)</bibRefCitation>
. For detailed taxonomic remarks on 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Galil" authorityYear="2009" box="[883,994,1000,1024]" class="Malacostraca" family="Leucosiidae" genus="Hiplyra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sagitta">
<emphasis box="[883,903,1001,1024]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[918,994,1000,1023]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">sagitta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
see 
<bibRefCitation author="Galil, B. S." box="[1046,1184,999,1023]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="279 - 320" refId="ref47241" refString="Galil, B. S. (2009) An examination of the genus Philyra Leach, 1817 (Crustacea, Decapoda, Leucosiidae) with description of seven new genera and six new species. Zoosystema, 31 (2), 279 - 320." type="journal article" year="2009">Galil (2009)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Naderloo, R. &amp; Apel, M." pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="248 - 258" refId="ref50320" refString="Naderloo, R. &amp; Apel, M. (2012) Leucosiid crabs of the genus Hiplyra Galil, 2009 (Crustacea; Brachyura; Leucosiidae) from the Persian Gulf and the Gulf of Oman with describing a new species. Zoological studies, 52 (2), 248 - 258." type="journal article" year="2012">Naderloo &amp; Apel (2012)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
